SIMPLE: inkle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inkle
<hw>In"kle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob.the same word as
<ets>lingle</ets>, the first <it>l</it> being mistaken for the definite
article in French. See <er>Lingle</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of tape or
braid.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inkle
<hw>In"kle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>inklen</ets> to hint;
cf. Dan. <ets>ymte</ets> to whisper.]</ety> <def>To guess.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧She <xex>inkled</xex> what it
was.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>R. D. Blackmore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inkling</ent>⟦br⟧
